{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/505", "repo": "rails", "body": "Let's agree that for vast majority of Rails applications, a \"partial update\" (a.k.a. `update_attributes`) is the most common use-case for an update-like request. Just imagine having to re-submit full representations of large/complex resources on every update (like nested attributes or **file attachments**).\r\n\r\nHaving said that, I'd vote for routing `PATCH` to the `update` action, and coming up with a separate action with `PUT` semantics (create/update full representations) in Rails 4.", "_id": {"$oid": "52385f14bd3543c151012142"}, "issue_id": 505, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3183396", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/505#issuecomment-3183396", "updated_at": "2011-12-16T22:19:34Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva", "login": "exviva", "gravatar_id": "56c0f984e7a1cccbd5ea165ef310ba4f", "html_url": "https://github.com/exviva", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/56c0f984e7a1cccbd5ea165ef310ba4f?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fa77d299ee00dfee2de17de8fcd02c69a.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 80070, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/exviva/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-12-16T22:19:34Z", "id": 3183396, "owner": "rails"}
